{{Infobox Organization | name = Django Girls | image = Djangogirls-logo.png | type = [[not-for-profit]] | key_people = {{plainlist| *Ola Sitarska *Ola Sendecka }} | website = {{URL|https://djangogirls.org}} }}
'''Django Girls''' is an international non-profit organization started by two Polish women, Ola Sitarska and Ola Sendecka,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.marieclaire.co.uk/life/16-women-doing-amazing-things-in-2016-14919|title=16 Women Doing Amazing Things in 2016|last=Proudfoot|first=Jenny|date=8 March 2016|work=Marie Claire|access-date=9 July 2017|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|language=en-US}}</ref> to inspire women from all backgrounds<ref name="rapidgrowth">{{Cite news|url=http://www.rapidgrowthmedia.com/innovationnews/022417-Django-Girls.aspx|title=Falling in love with programming: Django Girls inspires women to join the tech world|work=Rapid Growth|access-date=9 July 2017}}</ref> to get interested in technology and to become programmers,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Dillon|first1=Karen|title=Lawrence-born Django, which revolutionized website construction, celebrating its 10th anniversary|url=http://www2.ljworld.com/news/2015/jul/09/happy-birthday-django/|website=Lawrence Journal-world|access-date=17 June 2017}}</ref> offering a safe and friendly environment.<ref name="techspark">{{Cite web|url=https://techspark.co/django-girls-coming-cardiff-help-women-get-coding/|title=Django Girls is coming to Cardiff to help women get into coding -TechSPARK.co|website=techspark.co|language=en|access-date=9 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vam.ac.uk/articles/django-girls|title=V&A · Django Girls – Tech activists|website=Victoria and Albert Museum|language=en|access-date=9 July 2017}}</ref> It is known for the free workshops it hosts to help women to learn to program<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.onenewspage.com/video/20170425/7355456/Django-Girls-teaches-women-to-progam.htm|title=Django Girls teaches women to progam <nowiki>[sic]</nowiki>|work=One News Page|access-date=9 July 2017}}</ref> and for its [[Django (web framework)|Django]] tutorial.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Chilabert|first1=Hernán|title=Django Tutorials and Courses|url=https://hackr.io/tutorials/learn-django|website=hackr.io|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref> It is often supported by the [[Python Software Foundation]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sushinsky|first1=Mary Ann|title=PSF supports more Django Girls!|url=https://pyfound.blogspot.com.br/2015/04/psf-supports-more-django-girls.html|website=Python Software Foundation News|access-date=17 June 2017}}</ref>
== History == The first Django Girls workshop, which kicked off Django Girls, happened during EuroPython 2014, in [[Berlin]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=2015 Team|first1=EuroPython|title=Our next keynote: Ola & Ola (Django Girls)|url=http://blog.europython.eu/post/117337312602/our-next-keynote-ola-ola-django-girls|website=EuroPython Blog|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref> Ola Sitarska and Ola Sendecka decided to use Django and Python because both are open source code platforms and not subject to copyright, which may help women developing their own ideas.<ref name="kathimerini">{{Cite news|url=http://www.ekathimerini.com/168766/article/ekathimerini/community/django-girls-make-the-male-dominated-world-of-it-more-accessible-to-women|title=Django Girls make the male-dominated world of IT more accessible to women, By Matthaios Tsimitakis {{!}} Kathimerini|access-date=2017-07-09|language=en}}</ref> Since then, the initiative has spread worldwide,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www2.ljworld.com/news/2015/jul/09/happy-birthday-django/|title=Lawrence-born Django, which revolutionized website construction, celebrating its 10th anniversary|website=LJWorld.com|language=en|access-date=2017-07-09}}</ref> reaching countries like [[Argentina]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.diariopanorama.com/noticia/242196/invitan-al-taller-django-girls-santiago-estero|title=Invitan al taller "Django Girls" en Santiago del Estero - Diario Panorama|last=Panorama|first=Diario|website=www.diariopanorama.com|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.frm.utn.edu.ar/webgraduados/index.php/1235-taller-django-girls-en-pycon-argentina-2015-mendoza|title=Taller Django Girls en PyCon Argentina 2015 - Mendoza|last=User|first=Super|website=www.frm.utn.edu.ar|language=es-es|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref> [[Australia]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.startupdaily.net/2016/07/coding-workshop-django-girls/|title=European coding workshop Django Girls comes to Brisbane to teach women tech skills - Startup Daily|date=2016-07-04|work=Startup Daily|access-date=2017-07-09|language=en-US}}</ref> [[Bolivia]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://boliviaemprende.com/eventos/taller-django-girls-mujeres-podran-aprender-programar-gratis|title=Taller Django Girls: Mujeres podrán aprender a programar gratis|date=2015-08-21|work=Bolivia Emprende|access-date=2017-07-17|language=es-ES}}</ref> [[Brazil]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://idgnow.com.br/mobilidade/2016/02/15/django-girls-realiza-workshop-gratuito-de-programacao-no-brasil/|title=Django Girls realiza workshop gratuito de programação no Brasil - IDG Now!|date=2016-02-15|work=IDG Now!|access-date=2017-07-09|language=pt-br}}</ref> [[Colombia]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.elheraldo.co/entretenimiento/programacion-web-para-mujeres-en-barranquilla-366549|title=Programación web para mujeres en Barranquilla|date=2017-05-28|access-date=2017-07-10|work=El Heraldo|language=es-co}}</ref> [[Ecuador]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.elmercurio.com.ec/526210-mujeres-se-capacitan-en-programacion/|title=Mujeres se capacitan en programación|date=2016-05-01|work=Diario El Mercurio - Cuenca Ecuador|access-date=2017-07-17|language=es-ES}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://vistazo.com/seccion/tecnologia/taller-gratuito-de-programacion-para-mujeres-en-guayaquil|title=Taller gratuito de programación para mujeres en Guayaquil|date=2016-06-22|work=Vistazo|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.eltiempo.com.ec/noticias/cuenca/2/409962/mujeres-reciben-un-taller-sobre-programacion|title=Mujeres reciben un taller sobre programación|last=Tiempo|first=El|date=2017-03-26|work=El Tiempo|access-date=2017-07-17|language=es}}</ref> [[Ghana]],<ref name="technovagh">{{Cite web|url=https://technovagh.com/2017/06/19/event-django-girls-workshop-ispace-foundation/|title=Event: Django Girls Workshop At iSpace Foundation|last=Kuuire|first=Joseph-Albert|date=2017-06-19|website=Tech Nova|access-date=2017-07-09}}</ref> [[Nigeria]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://techpoint.ng/2016/01/20/django-girls-teach-women-programming/|title=Django Girls will teach Nigerian women how to code for free|date=2016-01-20|website=Techpoint.ng|access-date=2017-07-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://techpoint.ng/2016/07/08/django-girls-free-programming-workshop-hold-ota-august/|title=Django Girls’ free programming workshop to hold in Ota this August|last=Wordsmith|first=Writer at Techpoint {{!}} Creative|last2=Strategist|first2=Digital|date=2016-07-08|website=Techpoint.ng|access-date=2017-07-09}}</ref> [[United Kingdom]],<ref name="techspark" /> [[Peru]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://rpp.pe/peru/piura/jovenes-recorren-sudamerica-promoviendo-tecnologica-noticia-931815|title=Jóvenes recorren Sudamérica promoviendo tecnológica|work=RPP Noticias|access-date=2017-07-17|language=es}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://pymex.pe/eventos-empresariales/notas-de-prensa/taller-gratuito-de-programacion-para-mujeres-con-django-girls|title=Taller gratuito de programación para mujeres con Django Girls – Pymex|website=pymex.pe|language=es-ES|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref> [[United States]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/django-girls-teaches-women-progam-194140778.html|title=Django Girls teaches women to progam|last=|first=|date=2017-04-25|work=Yahoo News|access-date=2017-07-09|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name="rapidgrowth" /> [[Zimbabwe]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hararenews.co.zw/2016/03/django-girls-bring-coding-skills-to-harare/|title=Django Girls brings coding skills to Harare|last=Mazingaizo|first=Sharon|date=2016-03-07|website=Harare News|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-07-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.kaguvidigital.com/2016/11/django-girls-harare-2-apply/|title=Django Girls Harare to host 2nd workshop this November - Kaguvi Digital|date=2016-11-09|work=Kaguvi Digital|access-date=2017-07-09|language=en-GB}}</ref> and many others.
== Tutorial == The tutorial, which teaches how to create and deploy a blog application using Django, is maintained and updated by the Django Girls community, using Github. As of May 2018, the Django Girls tutorial has been published online in 14 languages<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tutorial.djangogirls.org/|title=Choose a language · Django Girls Tutorial|last=DjangoGirls|website=tutorial.DjangoGirls.org|language=en|access-date=9 July 2017}}</ref> besides its original English version. As of May 2018, more than 1,000,000 users have visited its website.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://kcur.org/post/django-celebrates-10-years-web-development-lawrence|title=Django Celebrates 10 Years Of Web Development In Lawrence|last=Newill|first=Cody|access-date=9 July 2017|language=en}}</ref>
== Django Girls workshops == Using a manual provided by the organization,<ref name="techspark" /><ref name="kathimerini" /> Django Girls volunteers offer free<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.popwebdesign.net/popart_blog/en/2015/11/coding-and-women-where-to-learn-to-code-for-free/|title=Coding and women: Where to learn to code for free?|date=2015-11-16|work=PopArt Studio|access-date=2017-07-09|language=en-US}}</ref> one<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.spacecubed.com/en/blog/read/159874717/perth-web-girls-blurring-boundaries-and-beating-the-gender-bias|title=Perth Web Girls: Blurring Boundaries and Beating the Gender Bias|work=Spacecubed|access-date=2017-07-09|language=en}}</ref> or two days workshops in many cities of the world, usually held during weekends.<ref name="rapidgrowth" /> It is aimed at complete beginners, teaching about HTML, CSS, Python and Django.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Tysnicka|first1=Agata|title=Django Girls: How 10Clouds Helps Get More Women into IT|url=https://10clouds.com/blog/django-girls-how-to-get-more-women-into-it/|website=10Clouds|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref> As of May, 2018 414 cities across 90 countries<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.siliconrepublic.com/careers/django-girls-dublin-april-rte-coding-grace?google_editors_picks=true|title=First Irish Django Girls coding event taking place this April|last=Gorey|first=Colm|date=2016-03-18|work=Silicon Republic|access-date=2017-07-09|language=en-GB}}</ref> have hosted Django Girls workshops, with [[Accra]],<ref name="technovagh" /> [[Athens]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://windycitygreek.com/greek-girls-technology/|title=Greek Girls Pave the Technology Path|date=2015-11-04|work=WindyCity Greek|access-date=2017-07-09|language=en-US}}</ref> [[Florence]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Corvino|first1=Nadia|title=Django Girls a Firenze: workshop di programmazione per donne e ragazze|url=http://www.softrevolutionzine.org/2017/django-girls-firenze/|website=Soft Revolutionzine|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref> [[Kathmandu]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://techlekh.com/django-girls-workshop/|title=Django Girls Workshop #3 Successfully Organized in Kathmandu {{!}} TechLekh|date=2016-10-10|work=TechLekh|access-date=2017-07-09|language=en-US}}</ref> [[Lagos]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Adeleke|first1=David|title=Django Girls is coming to Lagos. Ready your laptops ladies|url=http://techcabal.com/2016/01/18/django-girls-is-coming-to-lagos-ready-your-laptops-ladies/|website=Techcabal|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref> [[Lahore]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.morenews.pk/django-girls-workshop-in-lahore-apply-before-20th-may/|title=Django Girls workshop to be held in Lahore; apply before 20th May - More News|date=2016-05-12|work=More News|access-date=2017-07-09|language=en-US}}</ref> [[Oxford]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Keown|first1=Callum|title=Coding event gets more Oxford women into computer programming|url=http://www.oxfordmail.co.uk/news/15286291.Coding_event_gets_more_Oxford_women_into_computer_programming/|website=Oxford Mail|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref> [[São José dos Campos]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kyoshy|first1=Felipe|title=Workshop promove inserção das mulheres na área de tecnologia|url=http://www.meon.com.br/noticias/regiao/workshop-promove-insercao-das-mulheres-na-area-de-tecnologia|website=Meon|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref> among them. As of May 2018, over 14,000 women have attended Django Girls workshops held across the globe.
