The '''Emily M. Gray Award''' from the [[Biophysical Society]] in [[Rockville, Maryland]], is given in recognition of "significant contributions to education in biophysics."<ref name="awardsite">[http://www.biophysics.org/AwardsOpportunities/SocietyAwards/EmilyMGrayAward/tabid/500/Default.aspx Emily M. Gray Award page] (last visited Mar. 24, 2014).</ref> The award was established in 1997 and first awarded the year thereafter.
