The '''Indonesia Higher Education Network''' is an inter-[[university]] educational network in [[Indonesia]].  For the first phase of development, the network consists of 32 universities. The main ring of this network is located on the island of [[Java]], five universities as a backbone network connected using [[STM-1]] line with a total 155 Mbit/s of [[Bandwidth (computing)|bandwidth]] capacity. Those universities are the [[University of Indonesia]], the [[Bandung Institute of Technology]], the [[Institut Teknologi Sepuluh Nopember|Institute Technology Sepuluh November]], [[Gadjah Mada University]] and the [[Diponegoro University]].<ref>
{{id}} [http://www.inherent-dikti.net/ Official site of INHERENT on Indonesia Higher Education Department]</ref> It was active since 2006.<ref>https://www.republika.co.id/berita/nasional/umum/17/11/24/ozwra7423-kemristekdikti-kembangkan-konektivitas-jaringan-idren</ref>

Since 2013, INHERENT no longer active. INHERENT Network eventually replaced by Indonesia Research and Education Network (IDREN) in 2015. <ref>https://www.republika.co.id/berita/nasional/umum/17/11/24/ozwra7423-kemristekdikti-kembangkan-konektivitas-jaringan-idren</ref>

