'''John Engels''' (January 19, 1931 [[South Bend, Indiana]] - June 13, 2007 [[Vermont]]) was an American [[poet]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Huddle|first1=David|title=The Life of a Poet: John Engels, for Example|url=https://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-181150299.html|website=Hollins Critic|accessdate=September 7, 2016|date=1 June 2008|subscription=yes}}</ref>
==Life== John Engels graduated from [[University of Notre Dame]] in 1952. After Navy service, Engels studied at the [[University College, Dublin]], then graduated from the [[Iowa Writers' Workshop]], with an M.F.A. in 1957. He taught at [[St. Norbert College]], and [[Saint Michael's College]], [[Sweet Briar College]], [[Randolph-Macon Woman's College]], [[Middlebury College]], and [[Emory University]], and the [[University of Alabama]]. In 1995, he was Wyndham Robertson Chair at [[Hollins College]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pshares.org/authors/authordetails.cfm?prmAuthorID%3D450 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-09-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071103134925/http://pshares.org/Authors/authorDetails.cfm?prmAuthorID=450 |archivedate=2007-11-03 |df= }}</ref>
Engels' work appeared in ''Harper's,''<ref>{{cite web|title=John Engels {{!}} Harper's Magazine|url=http://harpers.org/author/JohnEngels/|accessdate=September 7, 2016|subscription=yes}}</ref> the ''New Yorker,'' <ref>{{cite web|title=The New Yorker Digital Edition : Mar 29, 1982|url=http://archives.newyorker.com/?i=1982-03-29#folio=CV1|website=archives.newyorker.com|accessdate=September 7, 2016|subscription=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The New Yorker Digital Edition : Apr 27, 1981|url=http://archives.newyorker.com/?i=1981-04-27#folio=CV1|website=archives.newyorker.com|accessdate=September 7, 2016|subscription=yes}}</ref> and many other prestigious journals.
==Awards== * 1976 Frost Fellow at Bread Loaf Writers Conference * 1979 [[Guggenheim Fellowship]] <ref>{{cite web|title=John Simon Guggenheim Foundation {{!}} John Engels|url=http://www.gf.org/fellows/all-fellows/john-engels/|website=www.gf.org|accessdate=September 7, 2016}}</ref> * 1986 [[National Poetry Series]], for ''Cardinals in the Ice Age'' * 1988 Poet in residence at [[The Frost Place]]
==Works== *[https://web.archive.org/web/20100505193554/http://www.poetryfoundation.org/archive/poem.html?id=177652 "Adam After the Ice Storm", ''Poetry Foundation''] *[http://www.pshares.org/issues/article.cfm?prmArticleID=475 "Love Poem--Describing the Austere Comfort of the Dream in Which Nothing Is Named", ''Ploughshares'', Spring 1977] *{{cite book| title=The Homer Mitchell place: poems| publisher=University of Pittsburgh Press| year=1968 }} *{{cite book| title=Blood Mountain| publisher=University of Pittsburgh Press| year=1977| isbn=978-0-8229-3289-5 }} *{{cite book| title=Weather-fear: new and selected poems, 1958-1982| publisher=University of Georgia Press| year=1983| isbn=978-0-8203-0654-4 }} *{{cite book| title=Cardinals in the Ice Age: poems| publisher=Graywolf Press| year=1987| isbn=978-0-915308-91-0 }} *{{cite book| url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uIrwZnwYxkoC&printsec=frontcover&dq=John+Engels#v=onepage&q=&f=false| title=Big water: poems| publisher=Globe Pequot| year=1995| isbn=978-1-55821-358-6 }} *{{cite book| url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vWQSD6MGiWQC&dq=John+Engels&printsec=frontcover&source=bl&ots=fdV0bhhSRH&sig=YhbUO4QPTWrZjNN2KX5fhzO0o2s&hl=en&ei=0vm3SvTSDNKvlAeygeXHDg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=10#v=onepage&q=&f=false| title=Sinking creek: poems| publisher=Globe Pequot| year=1998| isbn=978-1-55821-638-9 }} *{{cite book| title=House and garden| publisher=University of Notre Dame Press| year=2001| isbn=978-0-268-03056-8 }} *{{cite book| title=Recounting the seasons: poems, 1958-2005| publisher=University of Notre Dame Press| year=2006| isbn=978-0-268-02770-4 }}
